          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Understand HRM meaning",
            "Identify core HR functions"
          ],
          "content": "## Introduction to Human Resource Management\nHuman Resource Management (HRM) is the process of managing people in organizations effectively and efficiently to achieve organizational goals.\n\n### Objectives\n- Acquire and retain talent\n- Improve employee performance\n- Ensure employee satisfaction\n\n### Core Functions\n- Recruitment\n- Training\n- Performance management\n- Compensation\n\n### Importance\nHRM ensures that the right people are placed in the right roles and motivated to perform.\n\n### Example\nHiring skilled engineers and ensuring they are trained and motivated reflects HRM in action.",
          "examples": [
            "Hiring developers for a tech company",
            "Managing factory workforce efficiency"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Treating HR as administrative only",
            "Ignoring employee satisfaction"
          ],
          "qna": [
            {
              "q": "What is HRM?",
              "a": "Managing people to achieve organizational goals."
            },
            {
              "q": "What are HR functions?",
              "a": "Recruitment, training, performance, compensation."
            },
            {
              "q": "Why is HRM important?",
              "a": "Ensures effective workforce management."
            },
            { "q": "Objective of HRM?", "a": "Maximize employee performance." },
            { "q": "Example?", "a": "Hiring and training employees." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic_id": "t2",
          "title": "HRM Functions",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "estimated_time": "20 min",
          "prerequisites": ["t1"],
          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Understand managerial and operative HR functions",
            "Differentiate HR roles"
          ],
          "content": "## HRM Functions\nHR functions are divided into managerial and operative.\n\n### Managerial Functions\n- Planning\n- Organizing\n- Directing\n- Controlling\n\n### Operative Functions\n- Procurement\n- Development\n- Compensation\n- Maintenance\n\n### Importance\nEnsures structured HR operations.",
          "examples": [
            "Planning workforce needs",
            "Training programs for employees"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": ["Ignoring planning", "Focusing only on hiring"],
          "qna": [
            {
              "q": "What are managerial functions?",
              "a": "Planning, organizing, directing, controlling."
            },
            {
              "q": "What are operative functions?",
              "a": "Procurement, development, compensation."
            },
            {
              "q": "Why HR functions important?",
              "a": "Ensure smooth operations."
            },
            {
              "q": "Difference?",
              "a": "Managerial is strategic, operative is execution."
            },
            { "q": "Example?", "a": "Training employees." }
          ]
        }
      ]
